Reasoning: The paper deals with under-determined linear systems of equations with sparse solutions and focuses on the performance of $\ell_1$-minimization in finding such solutions. This falls under the category of signal processing and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with optimization problems in signal processing and communication systems. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as it deals with sparse learning and optimization techniques. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories as they deal with optimization problems in various contexts. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on algorithmic techniques, but rather on theoretical analysis of performance thresholds.
